replies.body:
b/c) i think it took me about 5 or so games (spaced over many weeks when she was on rotation) but it was just one random game as her i got super fed and realised how strong she was so i kept playing her and then began to get better and better so id say upwards of 5 but it can vary i suppose. in terms of difficulty i wouldnt say she's too hard but the important thing is to get her combo right
d) i actually find shes strong in both aspects  as her snowballing is rly good but the only downside is her ganks are pretty bad before 6 whereas when she goes mid she can be pretty reliable providing she doesnt get poked to death {{champion:101}} {{champion:63}} {{champion:112}} 
e) the most common  (probably) and seemingly most effective is Q(wait to see if it lands if not then u have to consider whether u wanna risk going in w/o second ult)>W(activate before engage)>R>E(to keep enemy close)>R and Q should be off cd again shortly
g) {{item:3020}} 
    {{item:3285}} get first ONLY if ur winning lane and/or got at least one kill with no deaths as the cost is quite expensive and its better to build defensively in lane first
{{item:3001}} should be rushed vs any ap champ and {{item:3157}} against ad, but u should definitely get zhonyas within first 3 items to make up for her lack of escape
{{item:3116}} the slow is good for chasing and provides a nice ap boost. the hp is also extremely beneficial as it provides more sustainability during fights so u arent deleted straight away
{{item:3151}} only if theres 3 or more tanky champs in the enemy team as ur damage output will be low otherwise. the hp is also good which is why i favour it over {{item:3135}} 
i personally dont get {{item:3115}} unless theres only 1 or 2 ranged champs as most of the time you'll be hitting with abilities rather than actually auto attacking, however if u end up split pushing (which as i said shes good at) this is a rly good choice
